body:
So I've been playing a fair bit of Nasus recently, and I'm pretty good now with getting through the game without feeding or dying heaps, just focusing on stacking. But it seems like every time I play him, the enemy lanes get super fed and wreck us. Even when I build loads of tank, they still delete me. I just feel like I can't hold out the game long enough to get super fed and carry. Any tips for me?

Also; regular baron buffed minions take 3 Qs from a 800 stacked Nasus with triforce to kill. So op.

{{champion:39}} {{champion:75}}

replies.body:
Frozen heart and Spirit visage are core on him, sheen item is situational and mostly a late game item

If against AD, rush {{item:3110}} 
If against AP, rush {{item:3065}} 

Then build tank depending on the enemy team, and finish off with a triforce/iceborn gauntlet.

Nasus is kited easily and since triforce is such a big investment early he just dies due to not being tanky, never rush iceborn gauntlet, the aoe pushes your lane making it harder to cs, and the aoe creep kills don't count towards stacks.

Also once you reach 400+ stacks start grouping and just getting stacks whenever you can.

Example late game build: {{item:3110}} {{item:3065}} {{item:3143}} {{item:3083}} {{item:3265}} {{item:3078}}
